#: ../../source/blog/2019/root-transition/index.rst:4
msgid ""
"Istio self-signed certificates have historically had a 1 year default "
"lifetime. If you are using Istio self-signed certificates, you need to "
"schedule regular root transitions before they expire. An expiration of a "
"root certificate may lead to an unexpected cluster-wide outage. The issue"
" affects new clusters created with versions up to 1.0.7 and 1.1.7."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/blog/2019/root-transition/index.rst:10
msgid ""
"See `Extending Self-Signed Certificate Lifetime "
"</docs/ops/configuration/security/root-transition/>`_ for information on "
"how to gauge the age of your certificates and how to perform rotation."
msgstr ""

